entry.title: Red Flag Warning issued May 19 at 2:54AM MDT until May 19 at 9:00PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM
entry.summary:
...CRITICAL FIRE WEATHER CONDITIONS MONDAY FOR SOUTHERN NEW MEXICO AND FAR WEST TEXAS...
.A passing upper-level trough will keep winds strong across the region again today. Strong winds aloft will mix down to the surface, and a surface trough to the east will result in strong winds at the surface. The result will be strong and gusty west to west- northwest winds, with gusts 45 to 55 mph at times. In addition, dry conditions remain with single digit minimum relative humidity across the lowlands, and low teens across the mountains. This will result in an afternoon of critical fire weather conditions today.
* AFFECTED AREA...Fire Weather Zone 055 Texas Fire Weather Zone 055 El Paso County, Fire Weather Zone 056 Texas Fire Weather Zone 056 Hudspeth County, Fire Weather Zone 110 Southwest Mountains/Gila NF/Apache NF/GLZ, Fire Weather Zone 111 Southwest Deserts and Lowlands/Las Cruces BLM/GLZ, Fire Weather Zone 112 South Central Lowlands and Southern Rio Grande Valley/BLM/GLZ and Fire Weather Zone 113 Capitan and Sacramento Mountains/Lincoln NF/LNZ.
* AFFECTED AREA...Southwest and South-Central New Mexico including Fire Weather Zones NMZ110, NMZ111, NMZ112, and NMZ113. This includes the Lincoln and Gila National Forests. Also, Far West Texas, including Fire Weather Zones TXZ055 and TXZ056 covering El Paso and Hudspeth Counties.
* TIMING...Today from Noon to 9 PM MDT.
* WINDS...West 25 to 35 mph with gusts 40 to 50 mph.
* RELATIVE HUMIDITY...Dropping to 7 to 10 percent across the lowlands, and 13 to 17 percent across area mountains.
* EXPERIMENTAL RFTI...5 to 7 or Critical to Extreme.
* IMPACTS...Any fires that develop will likely spread rapidly. Outdoor burning is not recommended.
entry.cap:areaDesc: Southwest Mountains; Southwest Deserts and Lowlands; South Central Lowlands And Southern Rio Grande Valley; Capitan And Sacramento Mountains; El Paso; Hudspeth

entry.title: Red Flag Warning issued May 19 at 2:53AM MDT until May 19 at 8:00PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM
entry.summary:
...RED FLAG WARNING IN EFFECT TODAY FROM NOON TO 8PM MDT FOR THE MIDDLE RIO GRANDE VALLEY, SANDIA AND MANZANO MOUNTAINS, AND WEST CENTRAL BASIN AND RANGE DUE TO STRONG WINDS, LOW HUMIDITY, AND HIGH FIRE DANGER...
.Another round of strong west winds and low humidity will create critical fire weather conditions this afternoon in southwestern and south-central New Mexico. Humidities will be higher than yesterday so the high fire danger will generally be limited to the southern portions of each of the zones in the Red Flag Warning. Gusty showers and an isolated storm or two may enhance winds in the Rio Grande Valley and Sandia and Manzano mountains during the afternoon hours. Winds will shift from the west to the northwest in the late afternoon behind a Pacific cold front.
* AREA AND TIMING...Middle Rio Grande Valley (Zone 106) and West Central Basin and Range (Zone 109) today from 12PM to 8PM MDT.
* 20 FOOT WINDS...West to northwest winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts to 50 mph on Monday.
* RELATIVE HUMIDITY...10 to 15 percent along and south of US 60.
* IMPACTS...Any fires that develop will likely spread rapidly. Outdoor burning is not recommended.
